column5: I'm thinking of heading up near Goderich on Friday night, can anyone give a report on the current conditions?  I"m thinking either 9 mile, Maitland or Ausable.  Has anything started running up yet?  Or any other tribs where they are running?  Thanks.  Andrew.
Slim pickin's there's just no water. Word of warning as well, some pretty heavy winds are forecasted for that area on Friday/Saturday.
Some recent pic's of the Maitland and Nine Mile taken from another board... Pictures tell the whole story, not a pretty sight.

was there thanksgiving weekend was sad caught lots of rock bass and gobies a few guys fishing close to the walkover bridge but not very much action was going on dont know how it would be now give goderich bait and tackle a call they can help you out heres the # (519) 524-7910 good luck
